Significance testing for H3K27ac peaks

last changed: 2023-08-29

For generating a DESeq data set a colData file is required containing information about the experiment. Note that the parameter time is required to be numeric which is essential for a meaningful significance testing. Thus, the required information were gathered in a matrix, as follows:

> colData.H3ac <- matrix(NA, nrow = 22, ncol = 3) %>% as.data.frame()
> rownames(colData.H3ac) <- colnames(m.H3ac)
> colnames(colData.H3ac) <- c("construct", "replica", "time")
> colData.H3ac$construct <- str_split_i(colnames(m.H3ac), "_", 1) %>% 
+   as.factor()
> colData.H3ac$replica <- str_split_i(colnames(m.H3ac), "_", 3) %>% 
+   as.factor()
> colData.H3ac$time <- str_split_i(colnames(m.H3ac), "T", 2) %>% 
+   str_split_i( "h", 1) %>% 
+   as.numeric()
> 
> colData.H3ac <- arrange(colData.H3ac, construct, time, replica)
> 
> paged_table(colData.H3ac)
> m.H3ac <- m.H3ac[ , rownames(colData.H3ac)]

Now that we have all required files, the DESeq data set can be constructed and the parameter design takes the parameters for the underlying model.

> H3ac.coverage <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(m.H3ac, 
+                                         colData.H3ac, 
+                                         design = ~ construct + replica + time)
> 
> saveRDS(H3ac.coverage, file = "./Data/raw_H3K27ac.rds")
> 
> head(H3ac.coverage)
## class: DESeqDataSet 
## dim: 6 22 
## metadata(1): version
## assays(1): counts
## rownames(6): chr1:181453-181717 chr1:777858-779502 ...

## rowData names(0):
## colnames(22): U2OS31_T0h_Rep1 U2OS31_T0h_Rep2 ... U2OS33_T4h_Rep2
##   U2OS33_T4h_Rep3
## colData names(3): construct replica time

Regularized-log transformation and PCA

Next, the data was scaled using the rlog transformation to stabilize the data against variance within the data.

> rlog.H3ac <- rlog(H3ac.coverage, blind = F)
> 
> saveRDS(rlog.H3ac, file = "./Data/rlog_H3K27ac.rds")
> 
> head(rlog.H3ac)
## class: DESeqTransform 
## dim: 6 22 
## metadata(1): version
## assays(1): ''
## rownames(6): chr1:181453-181717 chr1:777858-779502 ...
##   chr1:920444-922078 chr1:923270-926516
## rowData names(7): baseMean baseVar ... dispFit rlogIntercept
## colnames(22): U2OS31_T0h_Rep1 U2OS31_T0h_Rep2 ... U2OS33_T4h_Rep2
##   U2OS33_T4h_Rep3
## colData names(4): construct replica time sizeFactor

To validate the data the rlog-transformed data was used to plot a principal component analysis (PCA) and a heatmap with hierachial clustering.

> pca.H3ac <- plotPCA(rlog.H3ac, 
+                     intgroup = c("construct", "time"), 
+                     returnData = T)
> per.Var <- round(100 * attr(pca.H3ac, "percentVar"))
> 
> ggplot(pca.H3ac, aes(PC1, PC2, color = time %>% as.factor(), shape = construct, label = name)) +
+   geom_point(size = 3) +
+   geom_text_repel(size = 2.5) +
+   labs(x = paste0("PC1: ", per.Var[1], "% variance"), 
+        y = paste0("PC2: ", per.Var[2], "% variance"),
+        color = "time",
+        main = "PCA for H3K27ac after infection in hours") +
+   theme_bw()

> sample.dist <- dist(t(assay(rlog.H3ac)))
> m.dist <- sample.dist %>% as.matrix()
> colnames(m.dist) <- NULL
> 
> col <- colorRampPalette( rev(brewer.pal(9, "Blues")) )(255)
> 
> plot.heat <- pheatmap(m.dist, 
+                       clustering_distance_rows = sample.dist, 
+                       clustering_distance_cols = sample.dist, 
+                       col = col)

Significance testing (Likelihood ratio test - LRT)

To find significant peaks a likelihood ratio test (LRT) was used. This test compares 2 models, the full model (M ~ construct + replica + time) and the simpler model (M(s) ~ construct + replica). This results in peaks which show significant difference between those 2 models, in this case only peaks which significantly affect the larger model will score a low enough p-values. The output was then used to filter the rlog data for significant peaks (adjusted p value <= 0.05).

> H3ac.LRT <- DESeq(H3ac.coverage, test = "LRT", reduced = ~ construct + replica)
> 
> head(H3ac.LRT)
## class: DESeqDataSet 
## dim: 6 22 
## metadata(1): version
## assays(4): counts mu H cooks
## rownames(6): chr1:181453-181717 chr1:777858-779502 ...
##   chr1:920444-922078 chr1:923270-926516
## rowData names(27): baseMean baseVar ... deviance maxCooks
## colnames(22): U2OS31_T0h_Rep1 U2OS31_T0h_Rep2 ... U2OS33_T4h_Rep2
##   U2OS33_T4h_Rep3
## colData names(4): construct replica time sizeFactor
> res <- results(H3ac.LRT)
> 
> head(res)
## log2 fold change (MLE): time 
## LRT p-value: '~ construct + replica + time' vs '~ construct + replica' 
## DataFrame with 6 rows and 6 columns
##                     baseMean log2FoldChange     lfcSE      stat     pvalue
##                    <numeric>      <numeric> <numeric> <numeric>  <numeric>
## chr1:181453-181717   19.8295     -0.0274382 0.0708144  0.146171 0.70222137
## chr1:777858-779502  115.4950     -0.0931898 0.0495954  3.678751 0.05511012
## chr1:827213-827667   27.6409     -0.0240558 0.0694030  0.123165 0.72562641
## chr1:903806-905645  171.2062     -0.0775925 0.0456288  2.718311 0.09920291
## chr1:920444-922078   55.3373     -0.4053070 0.1330429  7.275346 0.00699074
## chr1:923270-926516  431.2111     -0.2907847 0.0853096  9.642893 0.00190086
##                         padj

## chr1:903806-905645 0.2764747
## chr1:920444-922078 0.0503011
## chr1:923270-926516 0.0207135
> res.sig <- res[which(res$padj <= 0.05), ]
> 
> rlog.H3ac.sig <- rlog.H3ac[rownames(res.sig), ]
> 
> saveRDS(rlog.H3ac.sig, file = "./Data/rlog_H3K27ac_sig.rds")
